  "root_text": {
    "ud3.9:0.1": "Udāna 3.9 ",
    "ud3.9:0.2": "Sippasutta ",
    "ud3.9:1.1": "Evaṁ me sutaṁ—",
    "ud3.9:1.2": "ekaṁ samayaṁ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṁ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme. ",
    "ud3.9:1.3": "Tena kho pana samayena sambahulānaṁ bhikkhūnaṁ pacchābhattaṁ piṇḍapātapaṭikkantānaṁ maṇḍalamāḷe sannisinnānaṁ sannipatitānaṁ ayamantarākathā udapādi: ",
    "ud3.9:1.4": "“ko nu kho, āvuso, sippaṁ jānāti? ",
    "ud3.9:1.5": "Ko kiṁ sippaṁ sikkhi? ",
    "ud3.9:1.6": "Kataraṁ sippaṁ sippānaṁ aggan”ti? ",
    "ud3.9:2.1": "Tatthekacce evamāhaṁsu: ",
    "ud3.9:2.2": "“hatthisippaṁ sippānaṁ aggan”ti. ",
    "ud3.9:2.3": "Ekacce evamāhaṁsu: ",
    "ud3.9:2.4": "“assasippaṁ sippānaṁ aggan”ti. ",
    "ud3.9:2.5": "Ekacce evamāhaṁsu: ",
    "ud3.9:2.6": "“rathasippaṁ sippānaṁ aggan”ti. ",
    "ud3.9:2.7": "Ekacce evamāhaṁsu: ",
    "ud3.9:2.8": "“dhanusippaṁ sippānaṁ aggan”ti. ",
    "ud3.9:2.9": "Ekacce evamāhaṁsu: ",
    "ud3.9:2.10": "“tharusippaṁ sippānaṁ aggan”ti. ",
    "ud3.9:2.11": "Ekacce evamāhaṁsu: ",
    "ud3.9:2.12": "“muddāsippaṁ sippānaṁ aggan”ti. ",
    "ud3.9:2.13": "Ekacce evamāhaṁsu: ",
    "ud3.9:2.14": "“gaṇanāsippaṁ sippānaṁ aggan”ti. ",
    "ud3.9:2.15": "Ekacce evamāhaṁsu: ",
    "ud3.9:2.16": "“saṅkhānasippaṁ sippānaṁ aggan”ti. ",
    "ud3.9:2.17": "Ekacce evamāhaṁsu: ",
    "ud3.9:2.18": "“lekhāsippaṁ sippānaṁ aggan”ti. ",
    "ud3.9:2.19": "Ekacce evamāhaṁsu: ",
    "ud3.9:2.20": "“kāveyyasippaṁ sippānaṁ aggan”ti. ",
    "ud3.9:2.21": "Ekacce evamāhaṁsu: ",
    "ud3.9:2.22": "“lokāyatasippaṁ sippānaṁ aggan”ti. ",
    "ud3.9:2.23": "Ekacce evamāhaṁsu: ",
    "ud3.9:2.24": "“khattavijjāsippaṁ sippānaṁ aggan”ti. ",
    "ud3.9:2.25": "Ayañcarahi tesaṁ bhikkhūnaṁ antarākathā hoti vippakatā. ",
    "ud3.9:3.1": "Atha kho bhagavā sāyanhasamayaṁ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yena maṇḍalamāḷo tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi. ",
    "ud3.9:3.2": "Nisajja kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi: ",
    "ud3.9:3.3": "“kāya nuttha, bhikkhave, etarahi kathāya sannisinnā, kā ca pana vo antarākathā vippakatā”ti? ",
    "ud3.9:4.1": "“Idha, bhante, amhākaṁ pacchābhattaṁ piṇḍapātapaṭikkantānaṁ maṇḍalamāḷe sannisinnānaṁ ayamantarākathā udapādi: ",
    "ud3.9:4.2": "‘ko nu kho, āvuso, sippaṁ jānāti? ",
    "ud3.9:4.3": "Ko kiṁ sippaṁ sikkhi? ",
    "ud3.9:4.4": "Kataraṁ sippaṁ sippānaṁ aggan’ti? ",
    "ud3.9:5.1": "Tatthekacce evamāhaṁsu: ",
    "ud3.9:5.2": "‘hatthisippaṁ sippānaṁ aggan’ti. ",
    "ud3.9:5.3": "Ekacce evamāhaṁsu: ",
    "ud3.9:5.4": "‘assasippaṁ sippānaṁ aggan’ti. ",
    "ud3.9:5.5": "Ekacce evamāhaṁsu: ",
    "ud3.9:5.6": "‘rathasippaṁ sippānaṁ aggan’ti. ",
    "ud3.9:5.7": "Ekacce evamāhaṁsu: ",
    "ud3.9:5.8": "‘dhanusippaṁ sippānaṁ aggan’ti. ",
    "ud3.9:5.9": "Ekacce evamāhaṁsu: ",
    "ud3.9:5.10": "‘tharusippaṁ sippānaṁ aggan’ti. ",
    "ud3.9:5.11": "Ekacce evamāhaṁsu: ",
    "ud3.9:5.12": "‘muddāsippaṁ sippānaṁ aggan’ti. ",
    "ud3.9:5.13": "Ekacce evamāhaṁsu: ",
    "ud3.9:5.14": "‘gaṇanāsippaṁ sippānaṁ aggan’ti. ",
    "ud3.9:5.15": "Ekacce evamāhaṁsu: ",
    "ud3.9:5.16": "‘saṅkhānasippaṁ sippānaṁ aggan’ti. ",
    "ud3.9:5.17": "Ekacce evamāhaṁsu: ",
    "ud3.9:5.18": "‘lekhāsippaṁ sippānaṁ aggan’ti. ",
    "ud3.9:5.19": "Ekacce evamāhaṁsu: ",
    "ud3.9:5.20": "‘kāveyyasippaṁ sippānaṁ aggan’ti. ",
    "ud3.9:5.21": "Ekacce evamāhaṁsu: ",
    "ud3.9:5.22": "‘lokāyatasippaṁ sippānaṁ aggan’ti. ",
    "ud3.9:5.23": "Ekacce evamāhaṁsu: ",
    "ud3.9:5.24": "‘khattavijjāsippaṁ sippānaṁ aggan’ti. ",
    "ud3.9:5.25": "Ayaṁ kho no, bhante, antarākathā hoti vippakatā, atha bhagavā anuppatto”ti. ",
    "ud3.9:6.1": "“Na khvetaṁ, bhikkhave, tumhākaṁ patirūpaṁ kulaputtānaṁ saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṁ pabbajitānaṁ yaṁ tumhe evarūpiṁ kathaṁ katheyyātha. ",
    "ud3.9:6.2": "Sannipatitānaṁ vo, bhikkhave, dvayaṁ karaṇīyaṁ—",
    "ud3.9:6.3": "dhammī vā kathā ariyo vā tuṇhībhāvo”ti. ",
    "ud3.9:7.1": "Atha kho bhagavā etamatthaṁ viditvā tāyaṁ velāyaṁ imaṁ udānaṁ udānesi: ",
    "ud3.9:8.1": "“Asippajīvī lahu atthakāmo, ",
    "ud3.9:8.2": "Yatindriyo sabbadhi vippamutto; ",
    "ud3.9:8.3": "Anokasārī amamo nirāso, ",
    "ud3.9:8.4": "Hitvā mānaṁ ekacaro sa bhikkhū”ti. ",
    "ud3.9:8.5": "Navamaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "ud3.9:0.1": "Heartfelt Sayings 3.9 ",
    "ud3.9:0.2": "Professions ",
    "ud3.9:1.1": "So I have heard. ",
    "ud3.9:1.2": "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery. ",
    "ud3.9:1.3": "Now at that time, after the meal, on return from almsround, several mendicants sat together in the pavilion and this discussion came up among them: ",
    "ud3.9:1.4": "“Who knows a craft? ",
    "ud3.9:1.5": "Who is studying which craft? ",
    "ud3.9:1.6": "Which is the best craft?” ",
    "ud3.9:2.1": "In answer, some said that ",
    "ud3.9:2.2": "elephant-craft is the best of crafts. ",
    "ud3.9:2.3": "Others said that the best craft is ",
    "ud3.9:2.4": "horse-craft, ",
    "ud3.9:2.6": "or chariot-craft, ",
    "ud3.9:2.8": "or archery, ",
    "ud3.9:2.10": "or swordsmanship, ",
    "ud3.9:2.12": "or arithmetic, ",
    "ud3.9:2.14": "or accounting, ",
    "ud3.9:2.16": "or calculating, ",
    "ud3.9:2.18": "or writing, ",
    "ud3.9:2.20": "or poetry, ",
    "ud3.9:2.22": "or cosmology, ",
    "ud3.9:2.24": "or geomancy. ",
    "ud3.9:2.25": "At that point the conversation among those mendicants was left unfinished. ",
    "ud3.9:3.1": "Then in the late afternoon, the Buddha came out of retreat and went to the assembly hall. He sat down on the seat spread out, ",
    "ud3.9:3.2": "and addressed the mendicants: ",
    "ud3.9:3.3": "“Mendicants, what were you sitting talking about just now? What conversation was left unfinished?” ",
    "ud3.9:4.1": "So the mendicants told him what they had been talking about when the Buddha arrived. The Buddha said, ",
    "ud3.9:6.1": "“Mendicants, it is not appropriate for you gentlemen who have gone forth out of faith from the lay life to homelessness to talk about such things. ",
    "ud3.9:6.2": "When you’re sitting together you should do one of two things: ",
    "ud3.9:6.3": "discuss the teachings or keep noble silence.” ",
    "ud3.9:7.1": "Then, understanding this matter, on that occasion the Buddha expressed this heartfelt sentiment: ",
    "ud3.9:8.1": "“Living without a craft, light, wanting what is best, ",
    "ud3.9:8.2": "with senses controlled, everywhere free; ",
    "ud3.9:8.3": "a migrant with no bastion, unselfish, with no need for hope, ",
    "ud3.9:8.4": "having given up conceit, wandering alone: <j>that is a mendicant.” "
  },
